{"id":62361,"date":"2021-01-18T17:41:47","date_gmt":"2021-01-18T12:11:47","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=62361"},"modified":"2021-02-26T15:23:30","modified_gmt":"2021-02-26T09:53:30","slug":"radhakishan-damani","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/radhakishan-damani\/","title":{"rendered":"Radhakishan Damani Wiki, Age, Wife, Children, Family, Biography &amp; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p lang=\"en\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damani.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-62597\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damani.jpg\" alt=\"Radhakishan Damani\" width=\"507\" height=\"443\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damani.jpg 687w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damani-300x262.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 507px) 100vw, 507px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Radhakishan Damani (RD) is an Indian businessman, investor, and stock trader. He is famous for founding the superstore chain DMart, that earned him the title of &#8216;Retail King of India.&#8217;<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce2b4263bf\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/label><input type=\"checkbox\"  id=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce2b4263bf\"  aria-label=\"Toggle\" \/><nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/radhakishan-damani\/#WikiBiography\" title=\"Wiki\/Biography\">Wiki\/Biography<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/radhakishan-damani\/#Physical_Appearance\" title=\"Physical Appearance\">Physical Appearance<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/radhakishan-damani\/#Family_Caste\" title=\"Family &amp; Caste\">Family &amp; Caste<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/radhakishan-damani\/#Parents_Siblings\" title=\"Parents &amp; Siblings\">Parents &amp; Siblings<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/radhakishan-damani\/#Relationships_Wife_Children\" title=\"Relationships, Wife &amp; Children\">Relationships, Wife &amp; Children<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/radhakishan-damani\/#Address\" title=\"Address\">Address<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/radhakishan-damani\/#Career\" title=\"Career\">Career<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/radhakishan-damani\/#As_a_Stockbroker\" title=\"As a Stockbroker\">As a Stockbroker<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/radhakishan-damani\/#As_an_Entrepreneur\" title=\"As an Entrepreneur\">As an Entrepreneur<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/radhakishan-damani\/#Net_Worth\" title=\"Net Worth\">Net Worth<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/radhakishan-damani\/#FactsTrivia\" title=\"Facts\/Trivia\">Facts\/Trivia<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"WikiBiography\"><\/span>Wiki\/Biography<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Radhakishan Damani was born in 1954 (<strong>age 67 years; as of 2021<\/strong>) in Bikaner, Rajasthan. He did his schooling in Mumbai, and then, he got himself enrolled in the University of Mumbai. He dropped out in the 1st year of his college where he was pursuing a Bachelor of Commerce. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_62361_1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_62361_1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/economictimes.indiatimes.com\/small-biz\/entrepreneurship\/radhakishan-damani-his-journey-from-dalal-street-punter-to-long-term-investor-to-entrepreneur\/articleshow\/58230305.cms?from=mdr\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">The Economic Times<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Physical_Appearance\"><\/span>Physical Appearance<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><strong>Hair Colour:\u00a0<\/strong>Salt &amp; Pepper (semi-bald)<\/p>\n<p><strong>Eye Colour:\u00a0<\/strong>Black<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damani-profile.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-62598\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damani-profile.jpg\" alt=\"Radhakishan Damani \" width=\"283\" height=\"770\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damani-profile.jpg 294w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damani-profile-110x300.jpg 110w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 283px) 100vw, 283px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Family_Caste\"><\/span>Family &amp; Caste<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Radhakishan Damani was born into a poverty-stricken Marwari family. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_62361_1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_62361_1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/economictimes.indiatimes.com\/small-biz\/entrepreneurship\/radhakishan-damani-his-journey-from-dalal-street-punter-to-long-term-investor-to-entrepreneur\/articleshow\/58230305.cms?from=mdr\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">The Economic Times<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Parents_Siblings\"><\/span><strong>Parents &amp; Siblings<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>His father, Shivkishanji Damani, was a stockbroker on Dalal Street. RD&#8217;s brother, Gopikishan Damani, is a stock trader and investor.<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Relationships_Wife_Children\"><\/span><strong>Relationships, Wife &amp; Children<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Mr. Damani is married to Shrikantadevi Radhakishan Damani. The couple has three daughters, Manjri Damani Chandak, Jyoti Kabra, and Madhu Chandak.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_62599\" style=\"width: 581px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-wife-at-the-listing-ceremony-of-Avenue-Supermarts-Limited-D-Mart.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-62599\" class=\" wp-image-62599\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-wife-at-the-listing-ceremony-of-Avenue-Supermarts-Limited-D-Mart.jpg\" alt=\"Radhakishan Damani's wife at the listing ceremony of Avenue Supermarts Limited (D-Mart)\" width=\"571\" height=\"344\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-wife-at-the-listing-ceremony-of-Avenue-Supermarts-Limited-D-Mart.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-wife-at-the-listing-ceremony-of-Avenue-Supermarts-Limited-D-Mart-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-wife-at-the-listing-ceremony-of-Avenue-Supermarts-Limited-D-Mart-768x462.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 571px) 100vw, 571px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-62599\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Radhakishan Damani&#8217;s wife at the listing ceremony of Avenue Supermarts Limited (D-Mart)<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_62601\" style=\"width: 479px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Madhu-Chandak..jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-62601\" class=\"wp-image-62601\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Madhu-Chandak..jpg\" alt=\"Radhakishan Damani's daughter Madhu Chandak\" width=\"469\" height=\"469\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Madhu-Chandak..jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Madhu-Chandak.-300x300.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Madhu-Chandak.-150x150.jpg 150w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Madhu-Chandak.-65x65.jpg 65w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 469px) 100vw, 469px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-62601\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Radhakishan Damani&#8217;s daughter Madhu Chandak<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_62602\" style=\"width: 494px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Manjri-Damani-Chandak.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-62602\" class=\" wp-image-62602\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Manjri-Damani-Chandak.jpg\" alt=\"Radhakishan Damani's daughter Manjri Damani Chandak\" width=\"484\" height=\"484\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Manjri-Damani-Chandak.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Manjri-Damani-Chandak-300x300.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Manjri-Damani-Chandak-150x150.jpg 150w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Manjri-Damani-Chandak-65x65.jpg 65w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 484px) 100vw, 484px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-62602\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Radhakishan Damani&#8217;s daughter Manjri Damani Chandak<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_62604\" style=\"width: 506px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Jyoti-Kabra.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-62604\" class=\" wp-image-62604\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Jyoti-Kabra.jpg\" alt=\"Radhakishan Damani's daughter Jyoti Kabra\" width=\"496\" height=\"474\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Jyoti-Kabra.jpg 628w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Radhakishan-Damanis-daughter-Jyoti-Kabra-300x287.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 496px) 100vw, 496px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-62604\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Radhakishan Damani&#8217;s daughter Jyoti Kabra<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Address\"><\/span>Address<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>He resides on Altamount Road in Mumbai with his family.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career\"><\/span>Career<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"As_a_Stockbroker\"><\/span><strong>As a Stockbroker<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>After dropping out of college, Mr. Damani started his ball-bearing business. At the age of 32, he quit this business due to the untimely demise of his father, and he joined his brother on Dalal Street as a stockbroker. When RD joined the stock market, it was ruled by the bear cartel of Manu Manek (also known as the Cobra). Mr. Damani learned to short sell the stocks from Manu, and later, he applied the same strategies to counter the bullish tactics of his nemesis <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/harshad-mehta\/#:~:text=Harshad%20Mehta%20was%20an%20infamous,Bombay%20Stock%20Exchange%20(BSE).\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Harshad Mehta<\/a>. It is rumoured that Radhakishan was a part of a bearish group called &#8216;triple-R&#8217; in the late &#8217;90s. The three Rs of the group were Radhakishan Damani, Raju (a chartist), and <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/rakesh-jhunjhunwala\/#:~:text=Rakesh%20Jhunjhunwala%20is%20one%20of,Street%20with%20a%20Midas%20touch.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Rakesh Jhunjhunwala<\/a> (the future Big Bull). Triple-R and Harshad Mehta were considered arch-rivals. Reportedly, they first fought over the stock of Apollo Tyres. Mr. Damani and Mr. Rakesh felt that the price of the stock of Apollo Tyres was heavily overpriced. So, they started short selling the stock, oblivious to the fact that Harshad was illegally rigging the stock&#8217;s price. RD and his group suffered heavy losses. Harshad Mehta was later found guilty of orchestrating the financial scam of 1992. In an interview, post the exposure of the scam, Mr. Damani said,<\/p>\n<blockquote><p>Agar Harshad saat din aur apni position hold kar leta, toh mujhe kathora leke road par utarna padta.\u201d<\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p>The Scam of 1992 led to a lot of investors and stockbrokers losing their money. RD helped many small scale investors by buying their depreciated shares. He also helped the clients of Deena Mehta (another famous stockbroker) after the Ketan Parekh Scam of 2001. In an interview, while talking about Mr. Damani\u2019s helpful gesture, Deena said,<\/p>\n<blockquote><p>When some of our clients got trapped in Videocon and BPL shares, RD helped us by taking over their positions\u2026 These scrips had become unsalable as there were no buyers in the market. RD is a very positive player in times of crisis. He\u2019s a shrewd investor; makes more money when he\u2019s bearish.\u201d<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_58659\" style=\"width: 551px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/The-Graph-stock-market-crash-due-to-the-1992-Harshad-Mehta-Scam.png\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-58659\" class=\" wp-image-58659\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/The-Graph-stock-market-crash-due-to-the-1992-Harshad-Mehta-Scam.png\" alt=\"The Graph of stock market crash due to the 1992 Harshad Mehta Scam\" width=\"541\" height=\"400\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/The-Graph-stock-market-crash-due-to-the-1992-Harshad-Mehta-Scam.png 640w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/The-Graph-stock-market-crash-due-to-the-1992-Harshad-Mehta-Scam-300x222.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 541px) 100vw, 541px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-58659\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The Graph of stock market crash due to the 1992 Harshad Mehta Scam<\/p><\/div><\/blockquote>\n<p>Mr. Damani&#8217;s multi-bagger stocks include VST Industries, HDFC Bank, Sundaram Finance, ITC, Gillette, Crisil, ICRA, 3M India, Blue Dart Express, Prozone Intu Properties, Uniply Industries, India Cements, and 1% stake in Andhra Paper. He invested in VST Industries Ltd. in 2000 when its stock was trading at around Rs. 80 per share. The share price soared to Rs. 3600 in 2020. Similarly, the share price of Sundaram Finance escalated from Rs. 270 per share to Rs. 1800 in 2021. Such investments helped Mr. Damani generate immense wealth.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_62606\" style=\"width: 622px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Rise-in-the-share-price-of-VST-Industries-Ltd.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-62606\" class=\"wp-image-62606\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Rise-in-the-share-price-of-VST-Industries-Ltd.jpg\" alt=\"The rise in the share price of VST Industries Ltd\" width=\"612\" height=\"376\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Rise-in-the-share-price-of-VST-Industries-Ltd.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Rise-in-the-share-price-of-VST-Industries-Ltd-300x185.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Rise-in-the-share-price-of-VST-Industries-Ltd-768x472.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 612px) 100vw, 612px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-62606\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The rise in the share price of VST Industries Ltd<\/p><\/div>\n<p>In 1995, HDFC Bank&#8217;s IPO went public, and RD bought Rs. 400 crores worth of shares at Rs. 40 per share; the share price is trading at Rs. 2600 as of 2020. In an interview, when he was asked why he chose HDFC Bank over a PSU Bank like SBI, Mr. Damani is rumoured to have said,<\/p>\n<blockquote><p>Dharavi Dharavi hota hai, aur Pedder Road Pedder Road\u2026 aage jaake HDFC ka bhaav dekh lena.\u201d<\/p><\/blockquote>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"As_an_Entrepreneur\"><\/span><strong>As an Entrepreneur<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>RD took a break from the stock market in the late &#8217;90s to focus on his retail business venture. In 2002, he started a hypermarket chain, DMart (registered as Avenue Supermarts Ltd.) with a single outlet in Powai. DMart has more than 200 stores spread across almost all over India as of 2020.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Strategy-behind-the-success-of-DMart.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-62607\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Strategy-behind-the-success-of-DMart.jpg\" alt=\"Strategy behind the success of DMart\" width=\"453\" height=\"566\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Mr. Damani went public with his retail chain in March 2017 with an offer price of Rs 299 per share, which skyrocketed to Rs 2900 in 2021. The market capitalisation of DMart rose from Rs 38,000 crore in March 2017 to Rs 1.6 lakh crore by June 2020, making it more valuable than Britannia Industries, Asian Paints, Bank of Baroda, and even Nestle.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_62608\" style=\"width: 610px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Rise-in-the-market-capitalisation-of-DMart.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-62608\" class=\"wp-image-62608\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Rise-in-the-market-capitalisation-of-DMart.jpg\" alt=\"The rise in the market capitalisation of DMart\" width=\"600\" height=\"297\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Rise-in-the-market-capitalisation-of-DMart.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Rise-in-the-market-capitalisation-of-DMart-300x149.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/01\/Rise-in-the-market-capitalisation-of-DMart-768x380.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-62608\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The rise in the market capitalisation of DMart<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Net_Worth\"><\/span>Net Worth<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Radhakishan Damani&#8217;s net worth is valued at around $20.5 Billion as of 2020. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_62361_1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[3]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_62361_1_3\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.forbes.com\/profile\/radhakishan-damani\/?sh=1efd1d7040de\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Forbes<\/a><\/span><\/span> His physical assets are listed as follows.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>a 156-room Radisson Blu Resort in Alibag, Maharashtra.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>a beachfront getaway home close to Mumbai.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"FactsTrivia\"><\/span>Facts\/Trivia<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/rakesh-jhunjhunwala\/#:~:text=Rakesh%20Jhunjhunwala%20is%20one%20of,Street%20with%20a%20Midas%20touch.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Rakesh Jhunjhunwala<\/a> (the Big Bull) deems Radhakishan Damani as his mentor. In an interview, talking about his mentor, Rakesh said,<br \/>\n<blockquote><p>I learnt trading from him \u2026 He has wisdom, extreme patience and humility \u2026 The patience he has to hear the other person\u2019s point of view is unbelievable \u2026 He taught me life and shaped my nature. If he and my father had not been there to guide me, I would not have achieved such success.\u201d<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_61147\" style=\"width: 568px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/Rakesh-Jhunjhunwala-with-his-mentor-Radhakishan-Damani.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-61147\" class=\" wp-image-61147\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/Rakesh-Jhunjhunwala-with-his-mentor-Radhakishan-Damani.jpg\" alt=\"Radhakishan Damani with his apprentice Rakesh Jhunjhunwala\" width=\"558\" height=\"330\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/Rakesh-Jhunjhunwala-with-his-mentor-Radhakishan-Damani.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/Rakesh-Jhunjhunwala-with-his-mentor-Radhakishan-Damani-300x177.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/Rakesh-Jhunjhunwala-with-his-mentor-Radhakishan-Damani-768x454.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-61147\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Radhakishan Damani with his apprentice Rakesh Jhunjhunwala<\/p><\/div><\/blockquote>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>He has conceded that the established investor Chandrakant Sampat is his inspiration. He learned a lot from the value investments of Mr. Sampat in the &#8217;80s and &#8217;90s.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>It is rumoured that RD predicted the tech bubble of 2001 and the global recession of 2008. The Tech bubble was the excessive use of the internet by the trading companies that led to the stock market crash.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Actor Paresh Ganatra played a role based on Radhakishan Damani in SonyLIV\u2019s hit web series Scam 1992: The Harshad Mehta Story. <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/Rakesh-Jhunjhunwalas-role-in-Scam-1992.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-61149\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/Rakesh-Jhunjhunwalas-role-in-Scam-1992.jpg\" alt=\"A snap shot from the series Scam 1992\" width=\"598\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/Rakesh-Jhunjhunwalas-role-in-Scam-1992.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/Rakesh-Jhunjhunwalas-role-in-Scam-1992-300x152.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/12\/Rakesh-Jhunjhunwalas-role-in-Scam-1992-768x388.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 598px) 100vw, 598px\" \/><\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>RD is the fourth richest Indian as of 2020 (Mukesh Ambani topped the list ).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Mr. Damani is referred to as Mr. White &amp; White by his family and close friends due to his love for white shirts and white pants.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Radhakishan Damani stays away from media interactions, and he is rarely seen at any stock market-related events.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>He loves to take a walk on Girgaum Chowpatty.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div class=\"489bcfb86580b123547338c91db0eff2\" data-index=\"3\" style=\"float: none; margin:3px 0 3px 0; text-align:center;\">\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\r\n     style=\"display:block\"\r\n     data-ad-format=\"autorelaxed\"\r\n     data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-6769524711517462\"\r\n     data-ad-slot=\"2473600074\"><\/ins>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"font-size: 0px; height: 0px; line-height: 0px; margin: 0; padding: 0; clear: both;\"><\/div><div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_label_expand_62361_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">References<\/span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_button_plus_62361_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">[+]<\/span><span><\/span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_button_minus_62361_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button collapsed\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_62361_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">[\u2212]<\/span><\/p><\/div> <div id=\"footnote_references_container_62361_1\" class=\"collapsed\"><table class=\"footnotes_table footnote-reference-container\"><caption class=\"accessibility\">References<\/caption> <tbody> \r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_62361_1_1\" class=\"footnote_backlink\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor_62361_1('footnote_plugin_tooltip_62361_1_1');\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>1,<\/a> <a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_62361_1_2\" class=\"footnote_backlink\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor_62361_1('footnote_plugin_tooltip_62361_1_2');\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>2<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/economictimes.indiatimes.com\/small-biz\/entrepreneurship\/radhakishan-damani-his-journey-from-dalal-street-punter-to-long-term-investor-to-entrepreneur\/articleshow\/58230305.cms?from=mdr\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">The Economic Times<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi pointer\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_62361_1_3\" class=\"footnote_backlink\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>3<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.forbes.com\/profile\/radhakishan-damani\/?sh=1efd1d7040de\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\">Forbes<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n <\/tbody> <\/table> <\/div><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Radhakishan Damani (RD) is an Indian businessman, investor, and stock trader. He is famous for founding the superstore chain DMart, that earned him the title of &#8216;Retail King of India.&#8217; Wiki\/Biography Radhakishan Damani was born in 1954 (age 67 years; as of 2021) in Bikaner, Rajasthan. He did his schooling in Mumbai, and then, he got himself enrolled in the University of Mumbai. He dropped out in the 1st year of his college where he was pursuing a Bachelor of Commerce. The Economic Times Physical Appearance Hair Colour:\u00a0Salt &amp; Pepper (semi-bald) Eye Colour:\u00a0Black Family &amp; Caste Radhakishan Damani was born <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":38,"featured_media":62597,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[19],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/62361"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/38"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=62361"}],"version-history":[{"count":7,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/62361\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":65436,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/62361\/revisions\/65436"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/62597"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=62361"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=62361"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=62361"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}